Muhammad [Wafā' ibn Muhammad al-Iskandarī al-Šādilī] (d. 765 H [1363 CE])

md:note.div:
Samling af Sufi-digte. Sandsynligvis alle skrevet af Wafā' ibn Muhammad al-Iskandarī al-Šādilī. Dette håndskrift formodentlig nedskrevet i 1600-tallet.
Erhvervet i Kairo i 1763 af Frederik Christian von Haven (d. 1763), der deltog i Carsten Niebuhr ekspeditionen til Mellemøsten (1761-1767).
Cod. Arab. 277

Collection af Sufi poems possible all writen by Wafā' ibn Muhammad al-Iskandarī al-Šādilī. Copied in the 17th Century.
Bought in Cairo in 1763 by Frederik Christian von Haven (d. 1763), a member of Carsten Niebuhr expeditionen to the Middle East (1761-1767).
